  • Constructor Details

    • DLNode

      public DLNode​(T element, DLNode<T> previous, DLNode<T> next)
      The constructor. Creates a node and puts it into place in the double linked list.
      Parameters:
      element - the element to be stored in the node
      previous - the node that will be before this node in the list, or null if no node is before this one
      next - the node that will be after this node in the list, or null of no node will be after this node
